<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Perry</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 23.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-30"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 30, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch of the 3d instant, No. 118,
                            communicating a copy of a note addressed to you by Mr. Pacheco, on the
                            subject of new regulations for vessels passing the forts of Tarifa, in
                            the straits of Gibraltar, has been received. Due publicity will be given
                            to this enlightened measure on the part of her Catholic Majesty’s
                            government.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Horatio J. Perry</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>